# HTML & Qute Standards

Templates live in `src/main/resources/templates/`. Static assets are served from `META-INF/resources/`.

## Document Skeleton

Every page must include:

```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>…</title>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="/css/….css">
</head>
```

- Load page scripts from `/javascript/…` in `<head>` or before `</body>`.
- Use **inline `<script>` only** for server-injected initial state (e.g. `let currentProject = {project.asJson.raw}`).

## Qute

- Control flow: `{#if}`, `{#for}`, `{#else}`, `{/if}` — match existing templates.
- Safe defaults for optional fields: `{project.name ?: 'No name'}`.
- Raw JSON injection uses `.raw` on escaped values: `{project.asJson.raw ?: '{}'}`.
- Comment blocks for dev placeholders: `{! … !}` — not shipped to the browser.

## Semantics & Accessibility

- Use semantic elements: `header`, `main`, `section`, `button` (not `div` clicks).
- Every interactive control needs an `id` when referenced from JS.
- Add `title` on truncated text (e.g. long filenames).
- Prefer `class` for styling; reserve `id` for unique hooks and ARIA when needed.

## CSS & Visual Identity

Load stylesheets in order:

```html
<link rel="stylesheet" href="/css/theme.css">
<link rel="stylesheet" href="/css/style.css">   <!-- main window -->
<link rel="stylesheet" href="/css/editor.css">  <!-- editor -->
```

See [`docs/DESIGN_SYSTEM.md`](docs/DESIGN_SYSTEM.md) and `.cursor/rules/visual-identity.mdc`.

| Pattern | Use |
|---------|-----|
| `btn`, `btn-primary`, `btn-secondary` | Buttons |
| `panel`, `panel-header`, `panel-body` | Main window and editor panels |
| `file-item`, `file-name`, `file-duration` | Media list rows |
| `project-table`, `status-row` | Main window projects and status |

Icons: `<svg class="icon"><use href="/icons/icons.svg#name"/></svg>` — no emoji in UI chrome.

- Do not use inline `style=""` for layout — add or extend rules in `/css/`.
- Section comments (`<!-- Header -->`) are welcome for large templates.

## Assets

- Theme: `/css/theme.css` (shared tokens and base components)
- Page styles: `/css/style.css` (main window), `/css/editor.css` (editor)
- Brand: `/brand/logo.svg`, `/brand/logo-icon.svg`, `/favicon.svg`
- Icons: `/icons/icons.svg` (SVG sprite)
- Scripts: `/javascript/index.js`, `/javascript/editor.js` — one entry script per page.
